<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1775,2016]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">
This species was described from “a small series” in the Horn Collection from 
<collectingRegion box="[1056,1149,1775,1800]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, with no other collecting data and no mention of a 
<typeStatus box="[436,484,1812,1836]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
designation. However, oddly, 
<bibRefCitation box="[826,981,1811,1836]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2419" refString="Cazier, M. A. (1940) New North American Acmaeodera, with synonymical and miscellaneous notes on other species. The Wasmann Collector, 4 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Cazier (1940)</bibRefCitation>
remarked that the 
<typeStatus box="[1191,1239,1812,1836]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
was lost, but that three specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[467,515,1848,1872]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
series were available in the Horn Collection at 
<collectionCode box="[1109,1181,1848,1872]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">ANSP</collectionCode>
. Horn’s collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,274,1883,1908]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
was moved to 
<collectionCode box="[441,520,1884,1908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">MCZC</collectionCode>
in October, 1974 (
<bibRefCitation box="[727,900,1884,1908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2377" refString="Bousquet, Y. (2012) Catalogue of Geadephaga (Coleoptera, Adephaga) of America, north of Mexico. ZooKeys, 245, 1 - 1722. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 245.3416" type="journal article">Bousquet 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[911,1088,1884,1908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2603" refString="Lawrence, J. F. (1973) Horn and Dietz collections move to Harvard. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 27, 151." type="journal article">Lawrence 1973</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation box="[1107,1328,1883,1908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2628" refString="Nelson, G. H., Walters, G. C. Jr., Haines, R. D. &amp; Bellamy, C. L. (2008) A catalog and bibliography of the Buprestoidea of America North of Mexico. The Coleopterists Society Special Publication, No. 4, i - iv + 1 - 274." type="book chapter">
Nelson 
<emphasis box="[1192,1248,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
listed the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1920,1944]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
depository as follows: “ 
<collectionCode box="[482,566,1920,1944]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">MCZC</collectionCode>
? 
<collectionCode box="[586,657,1920,1944]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">ANSP</collectionCode>
8193 (
<typeStatus box="[741,791,1920,1944]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
is lost).” 
<bibRefCitation box="[909,1101,1919,1944]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2264" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (2008 a) A World Catalogue and Bibliography of the Jewel Beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Uol. 1. Introduction; Fossil Taxa; Schizopodidae; Buprestidae: Julodinae-Chrysochroinae: Poecilonotini. Pensoft Series Faunistica No. 76. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow, 625 pp." type="book">Bellamy (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<collectionCode box="[1191,1265,1920,1944]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">ANSP</collectionCode>
8193 
<typeStatus box="[1341,1436,1920,1944]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">Neotype</typeStatus>
needed.” Apparently both followed 
<bibRefCitation box="[554,729,1955,1980]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" refId="ref2419" refString="Cazier, M. A. (1940) New North American Acmaeodera, with synonymical and miscellaneous notes on other species. The Wasmann Collector, 4 (1), 17 - 29." type="journal article">Cazier’s (1940)</bibRefCitation>
lead in thinking “the 
<typeStatus box="[975,1025,1956,1980]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
” to be lost. Two 
<typeStatus box="[1217,1315,1956,1980]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">syntypes</typeStatus>
have been found at 
<collectionCode box="[250,322,1992,2016]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">ANSP</collectionCode>
. We hereby designate as 
<typeStatus box="[638,740,1991,2016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall, 1899" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1899" box="[791,1163,1991,2016]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conoidea">
<emphasis box="[791,1043,1991,2015]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">Acmaeodera conoidea</emphasis>
Fall, 1899
</taxonomicName>
the specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1397,1991,2016]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4. 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1967,1990]" captionTargetBox="[309,1263,193,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[190,1376,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. 1–3, dorsal habitus: 1, lectotype Acmaeodera conoidea; 2, holotype Phaenops horni; 3, holotype Phaenops caseyi. 4, aedeagus of the latter." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439864/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) measuring 
<quantity box="[275,361,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
and labeled as follows: a small square blank card // Ariz. [p, white] // 
<emphasis box="[1153,1262,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Conoidea</emphasis>
, Fall., 
<typeStatus box="[1341,1389,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">type</typeStatus>
. [h] // 
<collectionCode box="[179,249,189,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<typeStatus box="[179,249,189,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">TYPE</typeStatus>
</collectionCode>
[p] // 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1899" box="[333,648,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conoidea">
<emphasis box="[333,590,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera conoidea</emphasis>
Fall
</taxonomicName>
, 8193 [h, red] // 
<typeStatus box="[860,1023,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1899" box="[1039,1353,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conoidea">
<emphasis box="[1039,1295,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera conoidea</emphasis>
Fall
</taxonomicName>
, desig. Westcott &amp; Bílý 2018 [p, red]. The second specimen, simply labeled “Ariz. [p]” as above, becomes a 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1432,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, as we designate on blue card. In our opinion, the selection of a 
<typeStatus box="[865,968,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this species is especially important in light of the fact that “the 
<typeStatus box="[437,487,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">type</typeStatus>
” was declared lost, and the species is considered to range from 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1300,295,320]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Arizona</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion box="[1338,1406,296,319]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Texas</collectingRegion>
, is quite variable, and may be confused with others, notably 
<taxonomicName authority="Fisher." authorityName="Fisher." box="[792,1159,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoneglecta">
<emphasis box="[792,1076,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera neoneglecta</emphasis>
Fisher.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
